.\" heirloom-port-lifecycle(7)
.TH HEIRLOOM-PORT-LIFECYCLE 7 "2026-07-02" "Heirloom Darwin port" "Port ALM"
.SH NAME
heirloom-port-lifecycle \- run the full port lifecycle in one command
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B make lifecycle
.SH DESCRIPTION
Runs
.BR heirloom-port-bootstrap (7),
.BR heirloom-port-configure (7),
.B make build
(delegates to upstream
.IR makefile ),
.BR heirloom-port-install (7),
and
.BR heirloom-port-verify (7)
in sequence. Stops on the first failure with the failing stage's
diagnostic.
.PP
Equivalent to:
.PP
.RS 4
.EX
make bootstrap && make configure && make build && \\
make install && make verify
.EE
.RE
.PP
Best used for a first-time install on a fresh Darwin machine. For
day-to-day rebuilds you usually only need
.B make
+
.BR "make install" .
.SH ENVIRONMENT
Inherits
.B PREFIX
and
.B ROOT
per
.BR heirloom-port-install (7).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
All stages passed.
.TP
.B >0
First failing stage's exit code.
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR heirloom-port-bootstrap (7),
.BR heirloom-port-configure (7),
.BR heirloom-port-install (7),
.BR heirloom-port-verify (7),
.BR heirloom-port-uninstall (7)
